Hardware Alignment & Cache Architecture
* Line Size: Align shared buffers to 64 bytes (Intel) or 128 bytes (Apple Silicon) via alignas(). This eliminates false sharing cache invalidation cycles. [1]
* Pre-allocation: Use fixed-size, statically allocated Ring Buffers or heap arrays allocated once at boot. Zero malloc/free or dynamic resizing on the hot path.
* I-Cache Constraints: Keep the consumer loop footprint under 32KB/64KB to fit entirely within the CPU's Level 1 Instruction Cache (L1i), avoiding instruction fetch stalls.

Data Layout (SoA Vectorisation)
* Format: Structure of Arrays (SoA). Flat, parallel primitive arrays (e.g., float* x, float* y) stored contiguously. [1]
* Memory Pointers: Use __restrict__ qualifiers on all data pointers. This proves to the compiler optimizer that arrays do not overlap, enabling automatic loop vectorisation. [1]
* Padding: Pad total array element counts to multiples of 4, 8, or 16 to prevent masking loops or handling fractional "remainder" elements at array tails.

Thread Communication & Synchronization
* Primitive: Lock-free, Single-Producer Single-Consumer (SPSC) or Multi-Producer Single-Consumer (MPSC) queues. [1, 2, 3, 4]
* Memory Fences: Use atomic indices (std::atomic<size_t>) with strict memory ordering semantics:
    * Producers write via std::memory_order_release to flush cached writes to the visibility of other cores.
    * Consumer reads via std::memory_order_acquire to guarantee subsequent memory actions read the absolute latest states. [1, 2, 3]
* Affinity: Pin the consumer thread to a specific High-Performance core index (P-core) via pthread_setaffinity_np or OS equivalents to bypass OS-driven thread migration and preserve L1/L2 cache locality.

Instruction Optimization
* Inlining: Apply strict compiler forcing attributes (__attribute__((always_inline)) or [[msvc::forceinline]]) to all internal consumer methods.
* Unrolling: Use #pragma unroll or explicit code repetition inside the vector loop to destroy induction variable increments, comparison operations, and branch prediction hazard overheads.
* Registers: Utilize compiler intrinsics explicitly (_mm_load_ps / _mm_add_ps for x86 AVX, or ARM NEON/AMX equivalents) to force direct utilization of wide 128/256-bit hardware execution units. [1]
